                <lg>
                    <l><hi type="italic">for the students of Mountjoy Prison</hi></l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>Let me dress you, stranger,</l>
                    <l>in this new suit cut from a quart of ironlight.</l>
                    <l rend="indent2">
                        <hi type="italic">(You may call it ‘moon’)</hi>
                    </l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>See how the fabric falls</l>
                    <l>like a spill of stars,</l>
                    <l>how the pleats unfold like threads of water.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>Wear this suit in honour of a wing.</l>
                    <l>Wear this suit despite the darkness that inhabits</l>
                    <l>and escapes every cell.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>Walk forward in the footsteps of Elatha</l>
                    <l>who emerged out of the sea</l>
                    <l>bearing five twisted metals around his neck</l>
                    <l>and for his son a hollow</l>
                    <l>of gold.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg>
                    <l>Hold open your trembling palms.</l>
                    <l>A city is a form of remembering.</l>
                    <l>You too are born of kings.</l>
                </lg>
            </body>
        </text>
